{"title_page": "Delta Charter High School", "text_new": "{{Infobox School \n| name = Delta Charter High School\n| motto = \"One student at a time, where success is the only option\"\n| established = 2001\n| type = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]]\n| grades = K-12\n| principal = George M. Vierra\n| city = [[Tracy, California|Tracy]]\n| state = California\n| country = United States <!-- do not wikilink this field; the infobox does it for you -->\n| students = 450\n| colors = Green and Silver\n| mascot = Dragon\n| streetaddress = 31400 S. Koster Road\n| zipcode=95304\n| website = http://www.deltahigh.com\n}}\n\n'''Delta Charter High School''' (DCHS) is located on the outskirts of [[Tracy, California]]. DCHS has a student population of about 300.<ref name=www>{{cite web | url=http://www.deltahigh.com/ |title=Official Delta Charter High School Homepage |accessdate= February 22, 2007}}</ref>\nIt is a [[Charter School]] focused on balancing a mix of both [[independent study]] and classroom instruction,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deltahigh.com/about.html |title=Official Delta Charter \"About\" Page |accessdate=February 22, 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071221033550/http://deltahigh.com/about.html |archivedate=December 21, 2007 }}</ref> and is accredited by the [[Western Association of Schools and Colleges]].<ref name=\"deltahigh.com\">{{cite web|url=http://deltahigh.com/infopacket.pdf |title=Official Delta Charter Informational PDF |accessdate=February 22, 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080509161439/http://www.deltahigh.com/infopacket.pdf |archivedate=May 9, 2008 }}</ref>\nIt also tailors \"Personal Learning Plans,\" or \"PLPs,\" for each individual student<ref name=\"deltahigh.com\"/> to maximize their learning experience. DCHS has an active [[Speech and Debate]] team, competing in the [[National Forensic League]] and in YFL tournaments. It also has volleyball, basketball, and soccer teams.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.deltahigh.com Delta Charter High School]\n\n{{coord missing|San Joaquin County, California}}\n\n[[Category:Tracy, California]]\n[[Category:High schools in San Joaquin County, California]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2001]]\n[[Category:Charter high schools in California]]\n{{California-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox School \n| name = Delta Charter High School\n| motto = \"One student at a time, where success is the only option\"\n| established = 2001\n| type = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]]\n| grades = K-12\n| principal = George M. Vierra\n| city = [[Tracy, California|Tracy]]\n| state = California\n| country = United States <!-- do not wikilink this field; the infobox does it for you -->\n| students = 450\n| colors = Green and Silver\n| mascot = Dragon\n| streetaddress = 31400 S. Koster Road\n| zipcode=95304\n| website = http://www.deltahigh.com\n}}\n\n'''Delta Charter High School''' (DCHS) is located on the outskirts of [[Tracy, California]]. DCHS has a student population of about 300.<ref name=www>{{cite web | url=http://www.deltahigh.com/ |title=Official Delta Charter High School Homepage |accessdate= February 22, 2007}}</ref>\nIt is a [[Charter School]] focused on balancing a mix of both [[independent study]] and classroom instruction,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deltahigh.com/about.html |title=Official Delta Charter \"About\" Page |accessdate=February 22, 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071221033550/http://deltahigh.com/about.html |archivedate=December 21, 2007 }}</ref> and is accredited by the [[Western Association of Schools and Colleges]].<ref name=\"deltahigh.com\">{{cite web|url=http://deltahigh.com/infopacket.pdf |title=Official Delta Charter Informational PDF |accessdate=February 22, 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080509161439/http://www.deltahigh.com/infopacket.pdf |archivedate=May 9, 2008 }}</ref>\nIt also tailors \"Personal Learning Plans,\" or \"PLPs,\" for each individual student<ref name=\"deltahigh.com\"/> to maximize their learning experience. DCHS has a active [[Speech and Debate]] team, competing in the [[National Forensic League]] and in YFL tournaments. It also has volleyball, basketball, and soccer teams.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.deltahigh.com Delta Charter High School]\n\n{{coord missing|San Joaquin County, California}}\n\n[[Category:Tracy, California]]\n[[Category:High schools in San Joaquin County, California]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2001]]\n[[Category:Charter high schools in California]]\n{{California-school-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "a > an", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delta_Charter_High_School"}
{"title_page": "1999\u20132000 Kilmarnock F.C. season", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football club season\n|club=[[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]]\n|season=[[1999\u20132000 in Scottish football|1999\u20132000]]\n|manager= [[Bobby Williamson]]\n|chairman=\n|stadium=[[Rugby Park]]\n|league=[[1999\u20132000 Scottish Premier League|SPL]]\n|league result='''Ninth place'''\n|cup1=[[1999\u20132000 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]]\n|cup1 result='''Third round''', lost to [[Alloa Athletic F.C.|Alloa Athletic]]\n|cup2=[[1999\u20132000 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]]\n|cup2 result='''Semi-final''', lost to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n|cup3=[[1999\u20132000 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n|cup3 result='''First round'''\n|league topscorer=[[Christophe Cocard|Cocard]] (8)\n|season topscorer=Cocard (8)\n|highest attendance=15,795 v [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]], SPL, 16 October 1999 \n|lowest attendance=6,002 v [[St. Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]], SPL, 18 December 1999\n|average attendance=9,419 \n|pattern_la1=_whiteshoulders\n|pattern_b1=_whitestripes4\n|pattern_ra1=_whiteshoulders\n|pattern_sh1=_bluesides\n|leftarm1=0000ff\n|body1=0000ff\n|rightarm1=0000ff\n|shorts1=\n|socks1=\n|pattern_la2=_blacklower\n|pattern_b2=_thinblacksides\n|pattern_ra2=_blacklower\n|pattern_sh2=_whitesides\n|pattern_so2=_4_hoops_thin_burgundy\n|leftarm2=660000\n|body2=660000\n|rightarm2=660000\n|shorts2=000000\n|socks2=\n|prevseason=[[1998\u201399 Kilmarnock F.C. season|1998\u201399]]\n|nextseason=[[2000\u201301 Kilmarnock F.C. season|2000\u201301]]\n}}\n\nThe [[1999\u20132000 in Scottish football|1999\u20132000 season]] was [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock's]] second season in the [[1999\u20132000 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]]. Kilmarnock also competed in the [[1999\u20132000 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]], [[1999\u20132000 Scottish League Cup|Scottish League Cup]] and the [[1999\u20132000 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]].\n\n\n\n==Summary==\n\n\n===Season===\nKilmarnock finished ninth in the [[1999\u20132000 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]] with 37 points. They reached the semi\u2013final of the [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]], losing to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.londonhearts.com/scores/a2000/kilmarnock2000.htm | title=Results for Kilmarnock for 1999\u201300 | publisher=londonhearts.com | accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> Kilmarnock also reached the third round of the [[Scottish Cup]], losing to [[Alloa Athletic F.C.|Alloa Athletic]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.londonhearts.com/scores/a2000/kilmarnock2000.htm | title=Results for Kilmarnock for 1999\u201300 | publisher=londonhearts.com | accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> and lost in the first round of the [[1999\u20132000 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]] to [[1. FC Kaiserslautern|1. FC Kaiserslautern]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.worldfootball.net/report/europa-league-1999-2000-1-runde-kilmarnock-fc-1-fc-kaiserslautern/ | title=Kilmarnock 0 2 1. FC Kaiserslautern | publisher=worldfootball.net | accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n\n''Kilmarnock's score comes first''\n\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#CCCCCC|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n\n===Scottish Premier League===\n{{Main article|1999\u20132000 Scottish Premier League}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%; text-align:center\"\n!Match!!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|1||31 July 1999||[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||A||1\u20132||48,074||[[Ally Mitchell|Mitchell]] 65'\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|2||7 August 1999||[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]||H||2\u20130||8,378||[[Garry Hay|Hay]] 38', 62'\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|3||15 August 1999||[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]]||A||0\u20132||4,681||\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|4||21 A