]] to [[1. FC Kaiserslautern|1. FC Kaiserslautern]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.worldfootball.net/report/europa-league-1999-2000-1-runde-kilmarnock-fc-1-fc-kaiserslautern/ | title=Kilmarnock 0 2 1. FC Kaiserslautern | publisher=worldfootball.net | accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n\n''Kilmarnock's score comes first''\n\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#CCCCCC|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n\n===Scottish Premier League===\n{{Main article|1999\u20132000 Scottish Premier League}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%; text-align:center\"\n!Match!!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|1||31 July 1999||[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||A||1\u20132||48,074||[[Ally Mitchell|Mitchell]] 65'\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|2||7 August 1999||[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]||H||2\u20130||8,378||[[Garry Hay|Hay]] 38', 62'\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|3||15 August 1999||[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]]||A||0\u20132||4,681||\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|4||21 August 1999||[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]||H||0\u20131||7,732||\n|-style=\"background: #FFFFCC;\"\n|5||29 August 1999||[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]||A||0\u20130||6,621||\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|6||12 September 1999||[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]||H||0\u20131||14,328||\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|7||19 September 1999||[[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]]||A||3\u20130||11,337||[[Mark Reilly|Reilly]] 12', [[Mike Jeffrey|Jeffrey]] 80', [[Ally McCoist|McCoist]] 90'\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|8||25 September 1999||[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]||H||0\u20132||7,433||\n|-style=\"background: #FFFFCC;\"\n|9||16 October 1999||[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||H||1\u20131||15,795||[[Mike Jeffrey|Jeffrey]] 73'\n|-style=\"background: #FFFFCC;\"\n|10||23 October 1999||[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]|